<paragraph id="8B9236F2FFF4636432FE898CFC4DF2E0" blockId="3.[174,1232,1604,1859]" lastBlockId="4.[166,1225,1245,1859]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="129" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
Diagnosis. Both sexes differs from similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF4636330E6898CF92DF1DD" authority="(Panzer, 1798)" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[763,1120,1734,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF4636330E6898CFEEAF1DC" box="[763,935,1734,1760]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Myolepta vara</emphasis>
(Panzer, 1798)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF463633672898CFD81F03E" captionStart="Figs 10–15" captionStartId="4.[166,205,1116,1138]" captionTargetBox="[283,1115,175,1084]" captionTargetId="figure-322@4.[283,1115,175,1084]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 10–15. Myolepta obscura (FIgs 10–12) and M. vara (FIgs 13–15) from Zakarpattia: 10, 13 — habitus of the males, dorsal view; 11–14 — habitus of the females, dorsal view; 12, 15 — heads of the males, frontal view (arrow shows the shining median strip of the face)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454614" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454614/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">FIgs 13– 15</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF4636332C189ADFC6BF03E" box="[220,294,1767,1794]" captionStart="Figs 16–21" captionStartId="5.[175,214,1220,1242]" captionTargetBox="[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetId="figure-239@5.[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 16–21.Females of Myolepta obscura (FIgs 16–18) and M.vara (FIgs 19–21) from Zakarpattia:16, 19 — head, lateral view; 17, 20 — hind femur, anterolateral view; 18, 21 — scutum and scutellum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454616/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">19–21</figureCitation>
) by the scutum and scutellum with long wooly upstanding pile (
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF46363365789ADF9D7F03E" box="[1098,1178,1767,1794]" captionStart="Figs 16–21" captionStartId="5.[175,214,1220,1242]" captionTargetBox="[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetId="figure-239@5.[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 16–21.Females of Myolepta obscura (FIgs 16–18) and M.vara (FIgs 19–21) from Zakarpattia:16, 19 — head, lateral view; 17, 20 — hind femur, anterolateral view; 18, 21 — scutum and scutellum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454616/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">FIg. 18</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF4636332B38842FC47F01D" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[174,266,1800,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF4636332B38842FC47F01D" box="[174,266,1800,1825]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with short reclined pile, as on 
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF463633065884DFF8FF01E" box="[632,706,1799,1826]" captionStart="Figs 16–21" captionStartId="5.[175,214,1220,1242]" captionTargetBox="[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetId="figure-239@5.[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 16–21.Females of Myolepta obscura (FIgs 16–18) and M.vara (FIgs 19–21) from Zakarpattia:16, 19 — head, lateral view; 17, 20 — hind femur, anterolateral view; 18, 21 — scutum and scutellum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454616/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">FIg. 21</figureCitation>
), hind margin of the scutellum with hairs as long as two thirds/three quarters the median length of the scutellum (
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF4636331F18862F974F07F" box="[1004,1081,1832,1859]" captionStart="Figs 16–21" captionStartId="5.[175,214,1220,1242]" captionTargetBox="[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetId="figure-239@5.[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 16–21.Females of Myolepta obscura (FIgs 16–18) and M.vara (FIgs 19–21) from Zakarpattia:16, 19 — head, lateral view; 17, 20 — hind femur, anterolateral view; 18, 21 — scutum and scutellum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454616/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">FIg. 18</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF46363366E8863F99DF07E" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[1139,1232,1833,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF46363366E8863F99DF07E" box="[1139,1232,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with hairs half as long as the median length of the scutellum, as on 
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF3636431A78B97F949F3C4" box="[954,1028,1245,1272]" captionStart="Figs 16–21" captionStartId="5.[175,214,1220,1242]" captionTargetBox="[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetId="figure-239@5.[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 16–21.Females of Myolepta obscura (FIgs 16–18) and M.vara (FIgs 19–21) from Zakarpattia:16, 19 — head, lateral view; 17, 20 — hind femur, anterolateral view; 18, 21 — scutum and scutellum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454616/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">FIg. 21</figureCitation>
), pleurae entirely pollinose (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF36364337F8BB4FC8DF22B" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[354,448,1278,1303]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF36364337F8BB4FC8DF22B" box="[354,448,1278,1303]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, pleurae shining except for proepimeron and anterior anepisternum), anterolateral surface of the hind femur with many hairs as long as the maximum width of the femur (
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF36364338A8A75FCA9F266" box="[407,484,1343,1370]" captionStart="Figs 16–21" captionStartId="5.[175,214,1220,1242]" captionTargetBox="[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetId="figure-239@5.[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 16–21.Females of Myolepta obscura (FIgs 16–18) and M.vara (FIgs 19–21) from Zakarpattia:16, 19 — head, lateral view; 17, 20 — hind femur, anterolateral view; 18, 21 — scutum and scutellum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454616/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">FIg. 17</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636430028A75FF31F264" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[543,636,1343,1368]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636430028A75FF31F264" box="[543,636,1343,1368]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with hairs half as long as the maximum width of the femur, as on 
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF36364336F8A15FCF3F246" box="[370,446,1375,1402]" captionStart="Figs 16–21" captionStartId="5.[175,214,1220,1242]" captionTargetBox="[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetId="figure-239@5.[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 16–21.Females of Myolepta obscura (FIgs 16–18) and M.vara (FIgs 19–21) from Zakarpattia:16, 19 — head, lateral view; 17, 20 — hind femur, anterolateral view; 18, 21 — scutum and scutellum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454616/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">FIg. 20</figureCitation>
), metasternum bare (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636430FC8A2AFE72F245" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[737,831,1376,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636430FC8A2AFE72F245" box="[737,831,1376,1401]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, metasternum pilose). 
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636436488A15F9DEF245" bold="true" box="[1109,1171,1375,1401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Male</emphasis>
also differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636433208ACBFCD6F2A6" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[317,411,1409,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636433208ACBFCD6F2A6" box="[317,411,1409,1434]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by narrow shining median facial strip (
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF3636431658ACAFE8BF2A7" box="[888,966,1408,1435]" captionStart="Figs 10–15" captionStartId="4.[166,205,1116,1138]" captionTargetBox="[283,1115,175,1084]" captionTargetId="figure-322@4.[283,1115,175,1084]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 10–15. Myolepta obscura (FIgs 10–12) and M. vara (FIgs 13–15) from Zakarpattia: 10, 13 — habitus of the males, dorsal view; 11–14 — habitus of the females, dorsal view; 12, 15 — heads of the males, frontal view (arrow shows the shining median strip of the face)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454614" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454614/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">FIg. 12</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF36364361F8ACBF912F2A6" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[1026,1119,1409,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF36364361F8ACBF912F2A6" box="[1026,1119,1409,1434]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, shining median strip broadening from facial tubercle upwards to almost twice its width, as on 
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF3636432BB8A8BFDBFF2E0" box="[166,242,1473,1500]" captionStart="Figs 10–15" captionStartId="4.[166,205,1116,1138]" captionTargetBox="[283,1115,175,1084]" captionTargetId="figure-322@4.[283,1115,175,1084]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 10–15. Myolepta obscura (FIgs 10–12) and M. vara (FIgs 13–15) from Zakarpattia: 10, 13 — habitus of the males, dorsal view; 11–14 — habitus of the females, dorsal view; 12, 15 — heads of the males, frontal view (arrow shows the shining median strip of the face)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454614" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454614/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">FIg. 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF52667AFFF3636432BB8B16FFDDF39B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454614" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6454614" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454614/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" startId="4.[166,205,1116,1138]" targetBox="[283,1115,175,1084]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8B9236F2FFF3636432BB8B16FFDDF39B" blockId="4.[166,1224,1116,1191]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">
Figs 10–15. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636433078B16FC8EF34D" authorityName="Becher" authorityYear="1882" box="[282,451,1116,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636433078B16FC8EF34D" box="[282,451,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Myolepta obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(FIgs 10–12) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636430718B17FFF5F34E" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[620,696,1117,1138]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636430718B17FFF5F34E" box="[620,696,1117,1138]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(FIgs 13–15) from Zakarpattia: 10, 13 — habitus of the males, dorsal view; 11–14 — habitus of the females, dorsal view; 12, 15 — heads of the males, frontal view (arrow shows the shining median strip of the face).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9236F2FFF3636432C68AA8FE30F07F" blockId="4.[166,1225,1245,1859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">
Additional features. Both sexes of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF36364307B8AA9FFABF2C0" authorityName="Becher" authorityYear="1882" box="[614,742,1506,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF36364307B8AA9FFABF2C0" box="[614,742,1506,1532]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636431668AA9FE9BF2C0" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[891,982,1507,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636431668AA9FE9BF2C0" box="[891,982,1507,1532]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the frons, scutum and scutellum with pale yellowish hairs (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636430878949FFB8F120" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[666,757,1539,1564]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636430878949FFB8F120" box="[666,757,1539,1564]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all hairs distinctly golden, as on 
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF36364366F8948F9F6F121" box="[1138,1211,1538,1565]" captionStart="Figs 16–21" captionStartId="5.[175,214,1220,1242]" captionTargetBox="[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetId="figure-239@5.[254,1151,174,1190]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 16–21.Females of Myolepta obscura (FIgs 16–18) and M.vara (FIgs 19–21) from Zakarpattia:16, 19 — head, lateral view; 17, 20 — hind femur, anterolateral view; 18, 21 — scutum and scutellum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454616/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">FIg. 21</figureCitation>
), tibiae with numerous long hairs at least as long as width of the tibia (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636431F9896EF90DF101" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[996,1088,1572,1597]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636431F9896EF90DF101" box="[996,1088,1572,1597]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tibiae with hairs all shorter than the width of the tibia), the basoflagellomere dark (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF363643629890EF9DEF161" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[1076,1171,1604,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF363643629890EF9DEF161" box="[1076,1171,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the basoflagellomere pale, as on 
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF3636433EA892EFF0FF143" box="[503,578,1636,1663]" captionStart="Figs 10–15" captionStartId="4.[166,205,1116,1138]" captionTargetBox="[283,1115,175,1084]" captionTargetId="figure-322@4.[283,1115,175,1084]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 10–15. Myolepta obscura (FIgs 10–12) and M. vara (FIgs 13–15) from Zakarpattia: 10, 13 — habitus of the males, dorsal view; 11–14 — habitus of the females, dorsal view; 12, 15 — heads of the males, frontal view (arrow shows the shining median strip of the face)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454614" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454614/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">FIg. 15</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF36364304A892EFFD9F142" bold="true" box="[599,660,1636,1662]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Male</emphasis>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636430A7892FFE71F142" authorityName="Becher" authorityYear="1882" box="[698,828,1636,1662]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636430A7892FFE71F142" box="[698,828,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636431CA892FF979F142" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[983,1076,1637,1662]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636431CA892FF979F142" box="[983,1076,1637,1662]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the frons with numerous upstanding hairs (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF36364304B89CCFFFFF1A3" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[598,690,1670,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF36364304B89CCFFFFF1A3" box="[598,690,1670,1695]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, frons almost bare with a few semi-adpressed hairs), width of the dusting frons edge along eyes is equal to the width of the orbital strip (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636432CC898DFC62F1DC" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[209,303,1735,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636432CC898DFC62F1DC" box="[209,303,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, width of the dusting frons edge along eyes less then the width of the orbital strip), frons angle between eyes acute (frons angle slightly obtuse in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636431C489ADF97AF03C" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[985,1079,1767,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636431C489ADF97AF03C" box="[985,1079,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF36364364D89ADF9E5F03D" bold="true" box="[1104,1192,1767,1793]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Female</emphasis>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636432BB8842FC64F01D" authorityName="Becher" authorityYear="1882" box="[166,297,1799,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636432BB8842FC64F01D" box="[166,297,1799,1825]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636433DB8842FF6EF01D" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[454,547,1800,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636433DB8842FF6EF01D" box="[454,547,1800,1825]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the frons with upstanding pile (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF3636431F48842F90AF01D" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[1001,1095,1800,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF3636431F48842F90AF01D" box="[1001,1095,1800,1825]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
frons with semi-adpressed hairs aside from the median line of the frons).
</paragraph>
